parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sudden Unintended Acceleration (Cruise Control and Throttle System Failure)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, especially when the vehicle is traveling at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates beyond the set cruise control speed
the brakes are ineffective in stopping the vehicle
the vehicle continues to accelerate even when the transmission is in park or neutral.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unwanted airbag deployment can cause unexpected and potentially dangerous situations, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Airbag deploys without any apparent reason
airbag deploys without any crash or impact

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can increase the risk of injury or fatality to occupants, compromising vehicle safety.
symptoms: Airbag does not deploy during a crash
airbag does not deploy during a front-end collision
airbag does not deploy despite sensor activation.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Loose or Faulty Under-Steering Column Trim Panel
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loose or faulty under-steering column trim panel can cause a distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents or loss of control, as the driver's feet may get caught under the panel, making it difficult to operate the pedals.
symptoms: The under-steering column trim panel falls onto the driver's feet while driving
the panel does not stay in place
the driver's feet get caught under the panel
the driver needs to pull over to adjust the panel
the panel does not lock into its designated position.
